.TH SELKIE 1 "2026-02-28" "selkie 0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
selkie \- a markdown viewer with GFM support and Mermaid chart rendering
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B selkie
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B selkie
is a graphical markdown viewer built with Zig and raylib. It supports
GitHub Flavored Markdown (GFM) via cmark-gfm including tables, task lists,
strikethrough, autolinks, and footnotes. It natively renders Mermaid
diagram types including flowcharts, sequence diagrams, class diagrams,
state diagrams, ER diagrams, Gantt charts, pie charts, mindmaps, gitgraph,
journey maps, and timelines.
.PP
Multiple files can be opened simultaneously in tabs. Markdown can also be
read from standard input by piping content to selkie or using the
.B \-
argument.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " PATH"
Load a custom theme from a JSON file.
.TP
.B \-\-dark
Use the built-in dark theme.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a brief help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show the version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-
Read markdown from standard input.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.BR j / k
Scroll down/up by line.
.TP
.BR d / u
Scroll down/up by half a page.
.TP
.B G
Jump to the bottom of the document.
.TP
.B gg
Jump to the top of the document.
.TP
.BR PageUp / PageDown
Scroll by a full page.
.TP
.BR Home / End
Jump to the top/bottom of the document.
.TP
.I numeric prefixes
Type a number before a navigation key to repeat it (e.g., 10j scrolls down
10 lines).
.SS Tabs
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open a file in the current tab (requires zenity).
.TP
.B Ctrl+T
Open a file in a new tab (requires zenity).
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Close the current tab.
.TP
.BR Ctrl+Tab / Ctrl+Shift+Tab
Cycle to the next/previous tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+1\fR through \fBCtrl+9
Switch directly to tab 1\-9.
.SS View
.TP
.BR Ctrl+= / Ctrl+\- / Ctrl+0
Zoom in, zoom out, or reset zoom level.
.TP
.B Ctrl+L
Toggle source line numbers in the gutter.
.TP
.B T
Toggle between light and dark themes.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+T
Toggle the table of contents sidebar.
.SS Search
.TP
.BR / " or " Ctrl+F
Open the search bar.
.TP
.BR Enter / Shift+Enter
Jump to the next/previous search match.
.TP
.B Escape
Close the search bar.
.SS Command Mode
.TP
.B :
Enter command mode (vim-style).
.TP
.B Enter
Execute the command.
.TP
.B Escape
Close the command bar.
.SS Editing
.TP
.B Ctrl+E
Toggle edit mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save the current file.
.SS Export
.TP
.B Ctrl+P
Export the document to PDF.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/selkie/themes/
User theme files.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Used to locate the
.BR zenity (1)
binary for file dialogs.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.B zenity
is an optional runtime dependency used for native file open dialogs
(Ctrl+O, Ctrl+T). If zenity is not installed, a notification is shown
and the file dialog is skipped. Install it with your package manager
(e.g.,
.B sudo dnf install zenity
or
.BR "sudo apt install zenity" ).
